heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 16.2mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 4th in our overall records.  The storm lasted 6.9 hours and 9.36mm of rain fell.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: On 04 January 2025, the rain lasted for 37.2 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  36.8mm accumulated and it fell at 4.6mm per hour at times.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.8°C), outside temperature (down 2.5°C), and inside temperature (down 1.9°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%) and rainfall (up 0.1 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 659 m), rainfall (down 0.1 mm), and light levels (up 5274 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1257 m), light levels (up 7218 lux), and rainfall (down 0.5 mm) when compared to today.
